Package net.myorb.math.matrices

Representations for Vectors and Matricies and implementations of their arithmetic operators.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    FullMatrixWrapper<T>
    wrap a master matrix to start tree of optimized cofactor processing
    MatrixAccess<T>
    principle methods used to represent access to matrix objects
    MinorAccess<T>
    modeling efficient minor matrix access assumes use of column 1 as the removed column for cofactor computation.
    SimultaneousEquations.AugmentedMatrix<T>
    description of a matrix appended with an additional row
    VectorAccess<T>
    provide access to spans treated as vectors
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AbstractMatrixWrapper<T>
    set default behaviors for implementations of matrix access
    Matrix<T>
    representation of matrix of generic cells
    MatrixOperations<T>
    operations available on matrix objects
    MatrixOperationsAccelerated<T>
    minor matrix mapping algorithm used to improve the comatrix and cofactor expansion execution
    MatrixSpaceManager<T>
    provide description of matrices as types for algebraic transform
    MinorMatrixWrapper<T>
    a wrapper for matrix class objects allowing minor matrix access modeled on top of full matrix.
    PolynomialFunctionOperations  
    SimultaneousEquations<T>
    methods for finding solutions to simultaneous equations
    SpanAccess<T>
    provide access to portions of large arrays treated as vectors
    Triangular<T>
    linear equation solutions for triangular matrices
    Vector<T>
    representation of vector of generic elements
    VectorOperations<T>
    operations available on vector objects
